548
00:42:11,300 --> 00:42:12,780
Your hands will get rough.

549
00:42:12,780 --> 00:42:14,950
It's okay.

550
00:42:24,850 --> 00:42:26,710
By the way...

551
00:42:26,710 --> 00:42:30,040
Since when did you start living with your grandma and uncle

552
00:42:30,040 --> 00:42:33,350
at my Soo Chul's place?

553
00:42:33,350 --> 00:42:35,940
Oh, when I was in eighth grade.

554
00:42:35,940 --> 00:42:39,910
Grandma was unable to find a job after getting older,

555
00:42:39,910 --> 00:42:42,770
so Step-Uncle at that time... Oh, no.

556
00:42:42,770 --> 00:42:46,780
Uncle graciously offered to let us live with him.

557
00:42:46,780 --> 00:42:50,220
What do you mean, "Step-Uncle?"

558
00:42:50,220 --> 00:42:54,730
Are you talking about my Soo Chul?

559
00:42:54,730 --> 00:42:56,770
Pardon?

560
00:43:00,180 --> 00:43:03,070
I heard this is your second marriage.

561
00:43:03,070 --> 00:43:06,270
Also, Dae Beom is not Soo Chul's biological son.

562
00:43:06,270 --> 00:43:08,490
Pardon?

563
00:43:08,490 --> 00:43:10,570
How did you know that...

564
00:43:10,570 --> 00:43:14,220
Why did you never tell me that you got remarried to Soo Chul with Dae Beom?

565
00:43:14,220 --> 00:43:18,090
I've been calling Dae Beom, the eldest son of this household all this time.

566
00:43:18,090 --> 00:43:21,720
How could you have never said a single word?

567
00:43:21,720 --> 00:43:25,680
Then after deceiving me like this,

568
00:43:25,680 --> 00:43:28,830
how could you continue to take my money like that?

569
00:43:28,830 --> 00:43:30,640
What do you mean by I deceived you?

570
00:43:30,640 --> 00:43:33,140
I just didn't tell you.

571
00:43:33,140 --> 00:43:35,680
I didn't ask for the allowance either.

572
00:43:35,680 --> 00:43:40,260
- You just gave it to me.
- Oh, my gosh.

573
00:43:40,260 --> 00:43:43,510
You're making me speechless.

574
00:43:43,510 --> 00:43:46,900
I'll say this since we're on the topic.

575
00:43:46,900 --> 00:43:49,650
Are you that unhappy about the little money you gave us?

576
00:43:49,650 --> 00:43:55,000
After losing Soo Chul, you must've kept all the money his parents left behind!

577
00:43:55,000 --> 00:43:57,340
Oh, my, my! Younger-sister-in-law!

578
00:43:57,340 --> 00:44:02,140
So I thought you were giving it conscientiously.

579
00:44:02,140 --> 00:44:03,980
Younger-sister-in-law!

580
00:44:03,980 --> 00:44:08,280
Are you saying that I took all of my parents' inheritance?

581
00:44:08,280 --> 00:44:12,380
You're saying that's why you diligently took the money I gave you?

582
00:44:12,380 --> 00:44:14,660
Look here, Younger-sister-in-law.

583
00:44:14,660 --> 00:44:17,500
How could you say something like that?

584
00:44:17,500 --> 00:44:22,900
All of my family's money was earned and left behind by my husband.

585
00:44:22,900 --> 00:44:24,620
My parents!

586
00:44:24,620 --> 00:44:26,810
I took care of them. I did!

587
00:44:26,810 --> 00:44:31,920
But how... how could you say something like that to me?

588
00:44:31,920 --> 00:44:34,250
What's all this about?

589
00:44:34,250 --> 00:44:37,560
Did you take money from my sister?

590
00:44:54,070 --> 00:44:57,660
I'm sorry, Noona.

591
00:44:57,680 --> 00:45:01,500
Why did you give her money?

592
00:45:01,510 --> 00:45:05,470
I... didn't want you to struggle.

593
00:45:05,470 --> 00:45:09,320
I gave it because of you.

594
00:45:09,320 --> 00:45:13,530
I never thought she'd think of it that way.

595
00:45:13,530 --> 00:45:17,060
Noona... I'm fine.

596
00:45:17,060 --> 00:45:20,170
I'll tell you if I'm struggling.

597
00:45:20,170 --> 00:45:23,840
So don't give stuff like that from now on.

598
00:45:27,470 --> 00:45:28,750
But Soo Chul.

599
00:45:28,750 --> 00:45:32,230
The fact that you got remarried,

600
00:45:32,230 --> 00:45:34,950
that Dae Beom wasn't your biological son,

601
00:45:34,950 --> 00:45:37,940
why didn't you tell me that?

602
00:45:40,160 --> 00:45:42,630
Noona...

603
00:45:42,630 --> 00:45:46,440
Why is that important?

604
00:45:46,440 --> 00:45:49,590
Dae Beom is my child too.

605
00:45:49,590 --> 00:45:52,660
Why is that not important?

606
00:45:52,660 --> 00:45:56,410
I don't know if you're too nice or stupid.

607
00:45:56,410 --> 00:45:58,960
Why do you live like this?

608
00:45:58,960 --> 00:46:03,870
You're breaking your back to fend for your wife's family by yourself.

609
00:46:03,870 --> 00:46:05,330
Forget about it.

610
00:46:05,330 --> 00:46:10,850
I don't want to talk anymore.

611
00:46:10,850 --> 00:46:14,520
I'm seriously so upset.

612
00:46:27,930 --> 00:46:29,800
Honey.

613
00:46:31,730 --> 00:46:35,060
How could you take money from my sister without me knowing?

614
00:46:35,060 --> 00:46:40,380
How dare you talk about our parents' inheritance?

615
00:46:40,380 --> 00:46:43,970
My sister got the chicken restaurant for us too. Do you even have a conscience?

616
00:46:43,970 --> 00:46:46,100
She seemed well off,

617
00:46:46,100 --> 00:46:49,260
so I thought she inherited your parents' money.

618
00:46:49,260 --> 00:46:51,880
That's why I spoke that way without thinking...

619
00:46:51,880 --> 00:46:53,970
But is that something to get this upset?

620
00:46:53,970 --> 00:46:56,080
People can make mistakes.

621
00:46:56,080 --> 00:46:59,340
Also, she gave money for us to use. How can I not take it?

622
00:46:59,340 --> 00:47:02,080
You should have told me, at least!

623
00:47:02,080 --> 00:47:05,820
If I had told you, you would've just gotten mad like this and not let me take it.

624
00:47:05,820 --> 00:47:10,830
Shouldn't we take that money and use it since we have none?

625
00:47:10,830 --> 00:47:12,090
What?

626
00:47:12,090 --> 00:47:16,430
I took the money because we need it so badly!

627
00:47:16,430 --> 00:47:18,050
Don't you even feel bad towards me?

628
00:47:18,050 --> 00:47:19,920
You're letting me live in a slum like this.

629
00:47:19,920 --> 00:47:24,090
Why are you making such a big deal over me taking that money?

630
00:47:24,090 --> 00:47:25,440
What did you say?

631
00:47:25,440 --> 00:47:27,430
You're the head of our household.

632
00:47:27,430 --> 00:47:30,460
Until when are you going to let us live in a house where rain leaks in?

633
00:47:30,460 --> 00:47:33,800
If you go to the US and suck it up for just five years,

634
00:47:33,800 --> 00:47:37,370
then we'll be able to buy a small house. But why won't you go?

635
00:47:37,370 --> 00:47:39,850
What's the reason you're not going?

636
00:47:39,850 --> 00:47:42,030
Go to the US and give us money! Money!!

637
00:47:42,030 --> 00:47:46,090
Then I wouldn't have to say something like this to Older-sister-in-law!

638
00:47:47,840 --> 00:47:51,740
How could you...

639
00:47:51,800 --> 00:47:53,990
Do you think I want to live taking money from others?

640
00:47:53,990 --> 00:47:56,500
I want to go to the US if I can go!

641
00:47:56,500 --> 00:48:00,490
Really!!

