00:50:00,080 --> 00:50:01,560
Hi!

671
00:50:01,560 --> 00:50:03,150
Why are you here again?

672
00:50:03,150 --> 00:50:05,000
Jo Sarah.

673
00:50:05,000 --> 00:50:07,910
I saw that you got engaged.

674
00:50:07,920 --> 00:50:09,420
What?

675
00:50:09,420 --> 00:50:12,920
I thought you looked different for some reason.

676
00:50:12,920 --> 00:50:17,050
You became the Madam of FT Group.

677
00:50:17,050 --> 00:50:19,670
You're covered in luxury brands.

678
00:50:19,670 --> 00:50:21,730
Did you take a shower with cash?

679
00:50:21,730 --> 00:50:24,630
Take your hands off!

680
00:50:24,640 --> 00:50:28,990
But how could you not even give me ten million won?

681
00:50:28,990 --> 00:50:31,530
After I pleaded with you like that.

682
00:50:31,530 --> 00:50:35,310
I bought you clothes, makeup,

683
00:50:35,310 --> 00:50:38,270
and luxury bags that you go crazy for.

684
00:50:38,270 --> 00:50:41,670
I treated you so well in the past.

685
00:50:41,670 --> 00:50:44,570
Let go of this!

686
00:50:44,590 --> 00:50:47,640
To get back to the point,

687
00:50:47,640 --> 00:50:49,870
just lend me 30 million won.

688
00:50:49,870 --> 00:50:54,570
You're going to become FT Group's Madam. Lending that much should be a piece of cake for you.

689
00:50:54,570 --> 00:50:57,340
- Let go! Let me go! Why are you doing this?
- Okay?

690
00:50:57,340 --> 00:51:01,420
- Lend me 30 million won.
- Oh, gosh!

691
00:51:06,930 --> 00:51:09,040
Hey. Let go of that hand.

692
00:51:09,040 --> 00:51:11,690
Who do you think you are to keep butting in?

693
00:51:17,320 --> 00:51:19,410
Are you saying that he hit you unprovoked?
[Detective Team 2]

694
00:51:19,410 --> 00:51:21,930
I'm telling you, yes.

695
00:51:21,930 --> 00:51:26,700
Detective. I'm never going to settle.

696
00:51:26,700 --> 00:51:29,610
Can't a person talk to another person?

697
00:51:29,610 --> 00:51:33,130
Just because I met up with my ex to talk,

698
00:51:33,130 --> 00:51:37,280
how can someone beat one to a pulp like this?

699
00:51:37,280 --> 00:51:42,030
Bastards like this who beat people need to serve time to come to their senses.

700
00:51:42,030 --> 00:51:45,060
I'm telling you again.

701
00:51:45,060 --> 00:51:47,990
I will never ever settle.

702
00:52:01,490 --> 00:52:03,460
The money was deposited safely.

703
00:52:03,460 --> 00:52:04,670
Thanks, Sarah.

704
00:52:04,670 --> 00:52:08,840
If you'd given the money initially, we wouldn't have had this bothersome situation.

705
00:52:10,320 --> 00:52:12,510
Don't ever show up in front of me again.

706
00:52:12,510 --> 00:52:14,490
Gosh, all right. I got it.

707
00:52:14,490 --> 00:52:17,570
FT Group Chairman's fiancée, Jo Sarah.

708
00:52:17,570 --> 00:52:20,720
Big congratulations on your engagement, once again.

709
00:52:20,720 --> 00:52:22,890
Take care.

710
00:52:28,260 --> 00:52:30,550
That bastard.

711
00:52:35,690 --> 00:52:38,400
Are you okay?

712
00:52:38,400 --> 00:52:41,340
Things got worse because of me.

713
00:52:41,340 --> 00:52:44,150
I'm sorry.

714
00:52:44,200 --> 00:52:48,480
No, it's fine. I really wanted to beat that guy to death,

715
00:52:48,480 --> 00:52:50,620
but you beat him good instead.

716
00:52:50,620 --> 00:52:54,960
So I was exhilarated.

717
00:52:54,970 --> 00:52:57,140
What did you say?

718
00:52:57,140 --> 00:53:02,040
Let's go, Ajussi. I'll buy you tofu.
 [T/N: It's a Korean tradition to eat tofu after being released from prison.]

719
00:53:02,040 --> 00:53:04,290
Let's go.

720
00:53:14,991 --> 00:53:17,051
You're home.

721
00:53:18,501 --> 00:53:20,861
Okay.

722
00:53:20,861 --> 00:53:23,421
Hurry up and go on in.

723
00:53:26,201 --> 00:53:28,831
Chief Jo. What's wrong?

724
00:53:28,831 --> 00:53:30,301
Ajussi.

725
00:53:30,301 --> 00:53:37,781
I only have two people I feel bad towards in the world.

726
00:53:37,781 --> 00:53:41,671
One of those people is you.

727
00:53:41,671 --> 00:53:46,511
I don't feel bad towards anyone in the world.

728
00:53:46,511 --> 00:53:51,161
But to you, I feel really bad.

729
00:53:52,971 --> 00:53:56,411
What's there to feel bad about towards me?

730
00:53:56,411 --> 00:53:59,261
I'm fine, so go inside now.

731
00:53:59,261 --> 00:54:02,701
I know you're not fine!

732
00:54:02,701 --> 00:54:06,581
I'm really lousy, pathetic,

733
00:54:06,581 --> 00:54:09,981
and a total scum.

734
00:54:09,981 --> 00:54:12,661
But why haven't you cussed me out once?

735
00:54:12,661 --> 00:54:17,311
That's making me feel even worse towards you.

736
00:54:22,591 --> 00:54:25,331
Who am I...

737
00:54:25,331 --> 00:54:28,701
to cuss you out?

738
00:54:32,541 --> 00:54:36,651
It's late.

739
00:54:36,651 --> 00:54:39,851
I'll get going first.

740
00:54:51,571 --> 00:54:54,741
J-Jo Sarah! Who's that punk?

741
00:54:54,741 --> 00:54:57,061
What does he do?

742
00:54:57,061 --> 00:54:59,651
I don't know either. I don't know him.

743
00:54:59,651 --> 00:55:01,291
What?

744
00:55:01,291 --> 00:55:04,801
You were hugging him as I looked on.

745
00:55:04,801 --> 00:55:07,241
When did I hug him?

746
00:55:07,241 --> 00:55:10,501
He's just someone who brought me home from the bar.

747
00:55:10,501 --> 00:55:12,651
That's it.

748
00:55:12,651 --> 00:55:17,101
You're crazy! What if someone sees you?

749
00:55:17,101 --> 00:55:19,071
Hey, you...

750
00:55:19,071 --> 00:55:21,561
Walk properly!

751
00:55:32,231 --> 00:55:36,901
- Chairman!
- Oh, gosh, you startled me.

752
00:55:36,901 --> 00:55:39,491
What are you doing here, Ms. Park?

753
00:55:39,491 --> 00:55:43,591
Were you waiting for me?

754
00:55:43,591 --> 00:55:44,921
No.

755
00:55:44,921 --> 00:55:47,691
Why would I wait for you, Chairman?

756
00:55:47,691 --> 00:55:50,201
I just...

757
00:55:50,201 --> 00:55:52,991
I got a little hungry after putting Se Jong to sleep.

758
00:55:52,991 --> 00:55:57,291
So I was on my way to buy ramen from the convenience store.

759
00:55:57,291 --> 00:55:59,401
But then why do you look so cold?

760
00:55:59,401 --> 00:56:02,481
You look frozen.

761
00:56:02,481 --> 00:56:05,381
I'm not.

762
00:56:05,431 --> 00:56:07,721
- It's cold. Let's go inside.
- No!

763
00:56:07,721 --> 00:56:11,781
Why don't you come with me? I'll get you cup noodles.

764
00:56:11,781 --> 00:56:13,931
Cup noodles?

765
00:56:16,781 --> 00:56:20,431
Did you not eat, Chairman?

766
00:56:20,431 --> 00:56:23,401
Well, I got caught up with work.

767
00:56:23,401 --> 00:56:26,891
But I'm fine. People skip meals on purpose to lose weight.

768
00:56:26,891 --> 00:56:30,821
It's not okay, Chairman! You can't even fall asleep if you're hungry.

769
00:56:30,821 --> 00:56:34,531
Let's go. I'll treat you!

770
00:56:42,901 --> 00:56:45,081
Ms. Park.

771
00:56:45,081 --> 00:56:47,911
- Are you really not cold?
- No.

772
00:56:47,911 --> 00:56:52,181
I'm not cold at all because I'm with you.

